node.text:
Let’s chat sensory materials! 🙌🏼 This year I’ve had a hard time finding sensory materials for my students to use due to safety + covid restrictions. #ad 

@discountschoolsupply offers a variety of sensory products at a low price for educators...we all love a good deal right? I’ve separated mine out into small containers for each student to use. Now that we are distance..I’m thinking these would be a perfect surprise to send home with my students in a supply pickup! ☺️

You can shop all the sensory materials from @discountschoolsupply at the link below! Let me know how you use them because I always need some fresh ideas!

https://tinyurl.com/y3t42rov

node.text:
Did y’all know @weareticonderoga has some of the coolest learning supplies? From the best #2 pencils around to whiteboard dice..they literally have it all! 🙌🏼⁣
⁣
I plan to use the whiteboard dice to practice the spelling patterns + sounds we are using in phonics. The best part is..when we move on to other sounds I can simply erase + write again!⁣
⁣
Do yourself a favor + check out the @weareticonderoga catalog..you will be pleasantly surprised! ☺️⁣
⁣
Side note: peep the frames behind me. They have been empty for 2 weeks because...hybrid teaching. Wonder how long they’ll stay like that? 🤷🏼‍♀️ 

@thetututeacher @apron_education @teachoutsidethebox @giftedteacher305 #ticonderogapartner #ad

node.text:
This teacher clearly doesn’t have “Big Teacher Energy” yet…hopefully it shows up soon 🤣

Either way..there is a TPT sale happening right now and my store is 25% off and since I’m a little late to the game I wanted to do a little giveaway! 

To win a $25 gift card to TPT + a $25 gift card to Target just like this post + comment with a resource you either love from my store OR one that you want! 👇🏻

Swipe to see some of my favorite resources from my store that I use daily in the classroom! 🧡

- Digital Party Pack
- Reading Skills Posters
- Writing Office
- Positive Notes to Students
- Need a Break Station
- Class/ Morning Meetings

Giveaway Closed!

node.text:
Black Hills photo dump 🏔 

Spending time with family, four wheeling, hiking, golfing, breweries + live music = the perfect little week away!

The more time I spend traveling..the more I wonder why I live in the suburbs surrounded by houses 🤣 I think I could live out here forever… 🧡

If you could move anywhere…where would it be?! 👇🏻

node.text:
Hello again 4th grade 👋🏻

I’m back + with my 6 boxes of upper elementary books that I didn’t get to use last year! 📚 I took a small amount of my chapter books with me to 2nd but am excited to dive back into these higher level books again. 

What’s your favorite upper elementary read aloud?! A few years ago I read the first book in the Masterminds series + my students loved it! 🙌🏼 

Lets compile a list together of some of your favorites! Comment below with your favorite read alouds + save this post to reference for later! 👇🏻

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Shaunda Wasik in Lakeville, Minnesota with @weareticonderoga, and @shopsimplylovely. May be an image of 1 person and indoor.

node.text:
✏️ Name a better pencil….I know, I can’t either! 

I know it’s only June, but I am fully prepared to make sure my students get in ALL of the writing this year after a year of hybrid + distance and there is no better way to do that than with @weareticonderoga 🙌🏼 #pencilsup 

This June @weareticonderoga is partnering with the @kidsinneed foundation to donate 3 million pencils to students in need. 🧡 I’m helping to spread the word and you can help too by:

✏️ Sharing this post 
✏️ Creating your own post using the hashtag #postforpencils 

Each post using the hashtag generates 20 pencils to the @kidsinneed foundation! Drop the ✏️ emoji below if you are participating so we can see how many pencils we can generate together! 🧡

node.text:
This year has been hard to allow flexibility in seating like I have in the past, but @moving.minds has always given me some simple solutions for that! 

The ShiftEd rocker + the Spring Seat from @moving.minds are great options for small movement while students sit at their desks, tables, or floor spots. I also love the Jitter Bands that they offer. They fit perfectly on my chair + are extremely durable! 🙌🏼

node.text:
I’m a little late to the pop it fidget trend...but they are making my small groups a little more exciting lately! 🙌🏼 Share all the ideas...how are you using them in your classroom?? 👇🏻

I am using decodable readers from Grade One Snapshots with most of my on level + below readers. Our quick group time goes a little something like this:

▪️ First, we practice the sight words + phonics pattern from the book. 
▪️ Then, students read the book a few times. 
▪️ Spell words that follow the pattern we are working on. Students touch spell with the pop it (their favorite part 😉) & write on our mini @_mcsquares_ whiteboards.
▪️ End with quick writing + a little comprehension!

Who knew a few simple tools could make reading group that much more engaging..which is exactly what I need at this time of the year!

node.text:
A little Friday weekly outfit post filled with all the feelings.. 🧡

Okay but I’m all seriousness...this week was a week and I am just thankful that I have the sweetest group of 2nd graders. 🥰

Sharing these things only because someone else may be in the same situation + know they aren’t alone. 🧡

This time of year is always stressful with staffing, but Covid has made it even more unknown for next year + I swear it’s all anyone talks about right now. I’m just trying to remember that I have a job + everything will turn out the way it is intended to no matter what grade level I end up in.🧡

Infertility Awareness Week is this week + I have a number of appointments coming up. It will be nice to finally (maybe) get some answers, but also a whole lot of nerves set in because of what they might be. Again, trying to tell myself that things happen for a reason + it will happen when it is supposed to 🧡

On top of all of that there was a lot going on in Minnesota this week and there is a lot of learning, healing & change that needs to be done in my state.

Sooo I am bringing you my outfits of the day because picking out outfits brings me joy...and I need a little bit of that in my life right now. 🥰 And if you’ve made it this far..thanks for being here. Sending love to anyone else who is feeling the weight of any of those same things 🧡🧡

node.text:
Is there anything better than reading at the beach?! Welcome to our Beach Day Read-A-Thon! 🏖

Each year our school holds a read-a-thon fundraiser. Students pledge to read a certain amount of minutes at school + their family & friends donate money to their read-a-thon. 📚 

This year we chose a beach theme! Swipe to get a peak inside  our beach themed day! 🥰

node.text:
Spicing up our Sonday phonics with some tracing manipulatives 🙌🏼

Our phonics program is based on Orton - Gillingham practices & while I love the benefits of it...it can be a bit route with its structure. We are constantly sound tracing words buuutt...sometimes getting an entire class to trace their words (in April) can be a task so...cue these super simple @dollartree finds!

🧡 Pencil case + salt
🧡 Garden Mats
🧡 Ziplock + Hair Gel

There’s always shaving cream...but we save that for special occasions...because it’s a lot 🤣What are some other items y’all use to spice up your phonics? Help a girl out! 😳

node.text:
Welcome to the Wasik Market! 💰Where everything is made out of paper + the sales people are full of smiles 😉

We ended our money + economics unit with a whole class market from @teachingmaddeness 🙌🏼 Each group created products out of paper, set their prices + created their storefront.

Students “earned” money to spend at the market over the past few weeks and were able to buy goods from the other stores in our market. 🧡

It was the perfect culmination activity to tie into our economics standards + the best way to keep engagement through the last 2 weeks before break! 🙌🏼

Now after all of this...I’m ready for a break 😜

node.text:
Mini magnetic whiteboard = instant engagement! These @_mcsquares_ mini-whiteboards are perfect for collaboration in the classroom. They are magnetic + stick to most magnetic surfaces! I love the added bonus with the colorful bands to keep them organized during collaboration.

We're going to use them to play The Amazing Race! Each group gets a color-coded whiteboard. They get a math problem, solve it + race to stick it on the chalkboard in the front of the room! A simple game that got a whole lot better with these mini whiteboards from @_mcsquares_ ! #ad

Head to the link in my bio to grab these AND use the code Shaunda15 at checkout to get 15% off! 🎉
